OL,3,CWater companies ask to hike bills by
OL,4,Cmore than first planned
OL,6,FWater companies have asked to hike
OL,7,Fconsumer bills by more than they
OL,8,Foriginally requested, according to
OL,9,Ffigures released by watchdog Ofwat
OL,10,Ftoday (Tuesday 22 October).
OL,12,FThe latest requests by water firms
OL,13,Fwould see the average consumer bill in
OL,14,FEngland and Wales rise by 40% between
OL,15,Fnow and 2030, costing #615 per year.
OL,17,FEarlier this year, companies asked
OL,18,FOfwat for bills averaging #585 by
OL,19,F2030, an increase of about one-third
OL,20,Ffrom the current average of #439.
